Calling all families.
Reminder, Golden City Elementary School will be having a "Back to School Night" this Thursday, August 20th. To try to spread everyone out and be as safe as possible, here are the details we need everyone to follow:
1. Come anytime between 2pm and 6pm.
2. Masks are recommended for all.
3. Social Distancing between all families is a priority.
4. To encourage social distancing, only one family in a classroom at a time. So please be respectful of others times by making your visit short.

Also, 7-12 if you have not been to the HS to get your schedule yet, please that this week.

See you next Tue the 25th for our first day of School.

Your responses will allow us to make decisions for the upcoming school year while prioritizing the health of our students and staff. Thank you for your support during this crazy, whirlwind of a year!

shared_text:
Barton County Health Department and Home Health Agency
June 3 at 5:17 PM ·

A COUNTY-WIDE School Physical & *School Shot Clinic is scheduled for July 1, 2020 from 1:00 – 4:00 pm at the Lamar High School, 503 Maple Street in Lamar, MO. Both clinics are for student athletes from the Golden City, Lamar, & Liberal school districts. Signed consent forms are required for physicals & shots - both forms MUST be signed by a parent or guardian. Check your school’s Facebook page & website for more information.

*Students entering the 8th & 12th grades are required by the
State of Missouri to have the following shots:

• 8th Grade: 1 dose of Tdap (tetanus, diphtheria, acellular
pertussis) & 1 dose of meningococcal (MCV4)

o 11 year olds can get the Tdap & MCV4 shots now & will be up-to-
date upon entering the 8th Grade!

• 12th Grade: 1 dose of meningococcal (MCV4)

o 16 year olds can get the MCV4 shot now & will be up-to-date
upon entering the 12th Grade!

The HPV shot will also be offered to students 11 – 18 years of age It is recommended by the CDC but is NOT a requirement for school attendance in Missouri.

post_text:
“When are we coming back to school?” I sure wish I had the answer to that question but after consultation with local school district leaders and health professionals, we have decided Golden City R-III Schools will remain closed until Friday, April 24. See also the letter attached for more details.
Based on all of the information we have available to us at this time and after consultation with many other area leaders, we are convinced this is our way to be part of the solution to stop the spread of this virus and protect the safety and welfare of our children, staff, and community.
We will try to continue to provide as much information as we know through our Facebook page and our website. We have also asked each of our teachers to contact our families to see how we can help you in this uncertain time. Please be patient and reach out to us whenever we can help answer your questions.
Be safe and stay Healthy
Mr. Rook

Sorry late but day 3 of the admin thought challenge
Today’s it’s Math from Mr Kaufman

There are six bunks in this picture. If four cows eat in each bunk how many cows do I have?

Half of the bunks had only 3 cows come up to eat and the other half had four. How many cows are at the six bunks?

One bunk of the six I have had no cows eating in it, two bunks had two cows, and three bunks had 5 cows each. How many cows are at the bunks?

There are thirty cows and I have six bunks to feed them. How many cows are at each bunk?

post_text:
As we have said before, we are very concerned with the safety and health of all of our community. We are trying to do some research on what is needed for our kids in the area of food. Here is the question. How many of our students would be in need of lunches during this time away from school?? We would not be able to provide a full hot meal, but would be possibly able to provide a meal in the way of things like sandwiches and fruit and possibly chips etc. To protect everyone and honor the guidance we have been given to keep us from having groups of people together, we would be doing this in some form of "to go" style bag lunch. We would also consider going to "pick up spots" throughout the district to get these to those students who need it.
If your children are in need of this type of arrangement, please call the Superintendents office to let us know that need and we will see what we can work out.
Thanks

Ok
Here is the best plan we can come up with for this messy situation
We get 150 tickets
Your current tickets are not valid
We are pulling out tickets for all the players to have their mom, dad, brothers and sisters to get tickets and be at the game.
That leaves us about 100 tickets
We will have a lottery style drawing for those 100 tickets.
We have the list of names of tickets purchased here and that list will be the start of the lottery list. You are in the drawing.

We will pull 50 names and each of those 50 will get 2 tickets.

If you did not buy tickets from us and you want to be in this lottery you have until 2:30 to come to school or contact us by phone to get on the list. You will have to meet us at JQH to pick up your tickets.

We also have a plan brewing to be able to live stream this game to the Plaza Theater in Lamar so any fans who do not get tickets can go see the game there for free

Final Four “pre-sell” tickets will also be sold out of our office this week as long as our allotment lasts. They are $9 at the door. Or they are also $9 at our office. If you buy them from us it just get you through the line to get in up there quicker. Also if you want to go both days that is two tickets for each person.
Hope that makes sense
